FT  07 FEB 92 / Parliament and Politics: News In Brief
AGRICULTURAL POLICY: The government's determination to resist changes in the
European Community's common agricultural policy which discriminated against
efficient UK farmers was reaffirmed by Mr John Gummer, agriculture minister,
in the Commons yesterday.
He said the next meeting to discuss the proposals made by Mr Ray MacSharry,
EC agriculture commissioner, would be on Monday.
*****
ARTHUR SCARGILL: National Union of Mineworkers' president Mr Arthur Scargill
has been dropped as an official of his constituency Labour party after being
vice-chairman for 10 years. He failed to win re-election in competition with
five other candidates in the Barnsley West and Penistone constituency in
South Yorkshire.
